# Legacy combined backend env example
#
# This repo now prefers one file per backend runtime:
# - core.env
# - node.env
# - media.env
#
# Start from these files instead:
# - backend/core.env.example
# - backend/node.env.example
# - backend/media.env.example
#
# You can still use a shared backend/.env for local-only convenience, but service-specific
# files are now the clean/default option, especially for GCP deployments.
